    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Warden-Captain Halvard is the commanding officer of Svellheim's Chainwarden toll-post on the Coastal Road. A veteran soldier whose authority comes from presence, not cruelty, he carries a chain-flail and heavy shield. He received a raven from Ashwright's network with a description of the party Ã¢â‚¬â€ he's been told to detain them alive, if possible, but has latitude. Halvard is a pragmatist who has been bribed, not a zealot. If the fight goes badly, he'll try to retreat.</p>",
      "director": "<p>Director note: Halvard carries a sealed letter from 'V.A.' (Voss Ashwright) describing the party and offering 50 gold for their detention Ã¢â‚¬â€ a key intelligence find and evidence that the Chainwardens have been compromised. He can be recruited as an ally if treated with respect.</p>",
